00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,660
Looking good up there,
Princess Twilight.

12
00:00:25,940 --> 00:00:28,820
Applejack, you know you
don't have to call me that.

13
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:30,520
Why do you protest so?

14
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:33,220
You've already given up
wearing your crown all the time,

15
00:00:33,260 --> 00:00:35,980
the least you can do
is embrace your new title.

16
00:00:36,060 --> 00:00:38,280
If other ponies want to
address me that way,

17
00:00:38,380 --> 00:00:40,200
I suppose it's fine. But...

18
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:41,780
not my friends.

19
00:00:41,790 --> 00:00:43,940
It just doesn't
feel right.

20
00:00:44,140 --> 00:00:44,700
<i>(sigh)</i>

21
00:00:44,710 --> 00:00:46,820
And neither does
all this flying business.

22
00:00:47,020 --> 00:00:49,540
The Summer Sun Celebration
is only two days away

23
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,800
and I'm never going to be
ready to perform my part.

24
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,720
Not if you spend all your
time down here you won't.

25
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:58,080
Now get up there and show
everypony the big finish!

26
00:00:58,550 --> 00:01:03,460
♪

27
00:01:03,470 --> 00:01:06,290
That's what
I'm talking about!

28
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,500
Waa-hoo!

29
00:01:09,730 --> 00:01:11,130
<i>(scream)</i>

30
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:12,770
<i>(grunts)</i>

31
00:01:13,370 --> 00:01:14,400
<i>(cough)</i>

32
00:01:14,410 --> 00:01:17,240
<i>(scream)</i>

33
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:20,110
<i>(zoom)</i>

34
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,610
<i>(scream)</i>

35
00:01:23,140 --> 00:01:24,410
<i>(crash)</i>

36
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:30,420
Wow! That was a big finish!

37
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:31,720
<i>(moan)</i>

38
00:01:40,461 --> 00:01:45,698
Subtitles by YayPonies
http://yayponies.eu
HoH version

39
00:02:07,220 --> 00:02:09,520
♪

40
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:16,400
♪

41
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,900
You look amazing, darling.

42
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,940
They've really captured
your regality.

43
00:02:21,980 --> 00:02:22,880
I suppose.

44
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:25,000
Oh, don't be so modest.

45
00:02:25,010 --> 00:02:27,720
<i>It's everypony's dream to</i>
<i>someday wear a crown</i>

46
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,480
<i>and have their coronation</i>
<i>ceremony preserved</i>

47
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,940
<i>in stained glass</i>
<i>for all to see.</i>

48
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:31,880
<i>(sighs)</i>

49
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,500
I don't know if it's
everypony's dream.

50
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,700
Most of my dreams
are about frosting.

51
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:37,400
<i>(slurp)</i>

52
00:02:37,460 --> 00:02:38,720
<i>(sigh of ecstasy)</i>

53
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,460
We'd better get going.

54
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:41,900
We don't want to
miss our train.

55
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,140
Fluttershy's
right.

56
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,060
Don't know about y'all

57
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:46,180
but I've still got bushels
to do to get ready.

58
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:48,600
The official celebration
may be here in Canterlot

59
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,780
but whoo-wee! has the
Mayor put us in charge

60
00:02:50,820 --> 00:02:52,960
of one heck of a
party back home.

61
00:02:54,820 --> 00:02:57,180
Aw, don't look like
that, sugarcube.

62
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:59,360
You get to be right there
with the other princesses

63
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,180
when Celestia
raises the sun.

64
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:01,920
And I'm honored.

65
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:03,100
Really I am.

66
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,620
It's just that the
Summer Sun Celebration

67
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,360
is what first brought
all of us together.

68
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,660
It just doesn't feel right
not getting to spend

69
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:11,980
such a special day with
my Ponyville friends.

70
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,940
It doesn't feel right
to us either, darling.

71
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:17,100
If the Mayor wasn't
so desperate for our assistance,

72
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:19,540
we'd most certainly
stay here in Canterlot.

73
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,360
<i>And of course we</i>
<i>do understand</i>

74
00:03:21,420 --> 00:03:23,620
<i>that your royal duties</i>
<i>must come first.</i>

75
00:03:23,630 --> 00:03:25,140
The Summer Sun
Celebration

76
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:26,600
may have brought
us together,

77
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,160
but it's something
much bigger

78
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:30,020
that'll always
keep us connected.

79
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:31,920
Exhibit A.

80
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:34,220
The six of us are
united by the

81
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,360
Elements of Harmony.

82
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:38,520
No amount of "royal duties"
is gonna change that.

83
00:03:38,940 --> 00:03:40,140
Right everypony?

84
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,140
<i>(Everypony confirm)</i>

85
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,880
Right, Pinkie Pie?

86
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,940
Creamy, creamy frosting.

87
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,980
<i>(slurp)</i>

88
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,540
You should take
that as a "yes".

89
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,040
<i>(train whistle)</i>

90
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:54,920
<i>PINKIE PIE: We're</i>
<i>going to write you</i>

91
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,120
and give you so
many details,

92
00:03:56,140 --> 00:03:57,760
it'll be like you're in
Ponyville with us!

93
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:58,900
Right, girls?

94
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,080
UNISON: Cross my heart
and hope to fly.

95
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:03,200
Stick a cupcake in my eye.

96
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:04,560
<i>RARITY: And you</i>
<i>will be with us</i>

97
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:06,100
right after the
celebration.

98
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:07,820
We already have an
appointment on the books

99
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,640
to discuss the royal
upgrades to your loft decor.

100
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:13,780
<i>CONDUCTOR: All aboard</i>
<i>for Ponyville!</i>

101
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:16,720
<i>(murmurs)</i>

102
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,700
Whee!

103
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,160
<i>(clattering train wheels)</i>

104
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:24,760
♪

105
00:04:24,770 --> 00:04:26,330
<i>(sigh)</i>

106
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,080
I can't help it, Spike.

107
00:04:28,180 --> 00:04:29,560
They've only been
gone a minute

108
00:04:29,620 --> 00:04:31,840
and I already feel like
I'm missing something.

109
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,520
For the Princess.

110
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,640
Dear Twilight, you
aren't missing anything.

111
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:38,200
Your friend, Pinkie Pie.

112
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,080
<i>PINKIE PIE: That's me!</i>

113
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,860
<i>Whoo whee! (laughter)</i>

114
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:44,220
But I am.

115
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,200
I just know it.

116
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:51,880
Check. Check. Check. Check.
And... check.

117
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,000
Huh. What do you know?

118
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,080
We're way ahead
of schedule.

119
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:56,780
I credit your extremely
competent assistant.

120
00:04:58,700 --> 00:04:59,600
So do I.

121
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:01,520
The Celebration isn't
until the day

122
00:05:01,580 --> 00:05:02,640
after tomorrow.

123
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:05,080
We could still fit in a
quick trip to Ponyville

124
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:06,400
and be back in
plenty of time

125
00:05:06,410 --> 00:05:08,800
to finish off these last few
things before the main event.

126
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:09,580
<i>(sigh)</i>

127
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,200
That would be nice, Spike.

128
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,720
But what if something
else came up

129
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:13,500
while we were gone?

130
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,460
What if we were delayed
getting back

131
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,760
and I wasn't able to finish
everything on that list?

132
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,760
What if we lost the list
on the way to Ponyville

133
00:05:19,780 --> 00:05:21,180
and then couldn't remember
which things we'd done

134
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,200
and which things
we hadn't done

135
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,680
and then spent so much
time trying to figure out

136
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:24,920
what we hadn't done
and what we had done

137
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,340
that we ruined the
entire celebration

138
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,640
by not doing the one
really important thing

139
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,720
that we were supposed to do?

140
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:29,340
<i>(clang)</i>
that we were supposed to do?

141
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:29,440
<i>(clang)</i>

142
00:05:29,450 --> 00:05:29,500
<i>(thud)</i>
<i>(clang)</i>

143
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,400
<i>(thud)</i>

144
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:33,040
Uh, so that's a "no", then?

145
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:35,820
These are the first royal
duties Princess Celestia

146
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,580
has given me.

147
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:38,620
I can't risk
letting her down.

148
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:41,040
<i>CELESTIA: And I'm</i>
<i>sure you won't.</i>

149
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:43,320
♪

150
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,660
Your Highness!

151
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:49,460
No need for that now,
Princess Twilight.

152
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:50,680
Sorry.

153
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,220
(giggle)

154
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,160
No need
to apologize.

155
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,280
Sorry.

156
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:58,500
I must admit that it is
wonderful to actually

157
00:05:58,540 --> 00:06:01,480
be looking forward to the
Summer Sun Celebration.

158
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,740
What do you mean?

159
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:05,520
For my subjects it has
always been a celebration

160
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:08,880
of my defeat of Nightmare
Moon, but for me?

161
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:09,500
(sigh)

162
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,180
It was just a
terrible reminder

163
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,240
that I'd had to
banish my own sister.

164
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:17,400
I guess I'd never really
thought about it that way.

165
00:06:17,780 --> 00:06:20,020
But now it has become a
wonderful reminder

166
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:23,180
of her transformation
back into Princess Luna

167
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,880
and our happy reunion.

168
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:27,560
I am so pleased that you
will be playing a role

169
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,800
in the festivities.

170
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:30,520
I know it must have
been difficult

171
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:33,060
to see your friends return
to Ponyville without you.

172
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,380
Maybe a little.

173
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,540
You may no longer
be my student,

174
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:37,580
Princess Twilight,

175
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,980
but I hope you know that
I will always be here

176
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,080
if you need me.

177
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,140
Just as I hope that you
will always be there

178
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,480
when I need you.

179
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,360
<i>(Spike clears his throat)</i>

180
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,340
I think this guy
needs you.

181
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,240
A message for
Princess Twilight.

182
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,360
<i>(party noisemakers)</i>

183
00:06:55,460 --> 00:06:57,320
A letter from
Ponyville, I presume?

184
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:58,820
Never mind.

185
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,260
It's not important.

186
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,160
Spike, where were we?

187
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,880
About to call it a night?

188
00:07:03,940 --> 00:07:06,880
We should probably go over
the checklist one more time.

189
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,420
I knew you were
gonna say that.

190
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,260
I'll leave you to it.

191
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:13,380
<i>(clicking footsteps)</i>

192
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:18,840
<i>♪ (threatening theme) </i>

193
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,580
<i>(crackling)</i>

194
00:07:22,540 --> 00:07:23,340
<i>(gasp)</i>

195
00:07:23,350 --> 00:07:24,440
<i>(scream)</i>

196
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:33,820
Huh?

197
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:34,420
Spike?

198
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,200
<i>(snoring)</i>

199
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,820
Check. Check. Check. Check.

200
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:37,540
Spike!

201
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:39,340
<i>(stretching groa)</i>

202
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,920
What time is it?

203
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,500
It's the middle
of the night.

204
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:43,820
But it could
be morning.

205
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:44,600
That's just it.

206
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,280
I can't tell.

207
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:50,260
Whoa. That is weird!

208
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:51,440
Come on, Spike.

209
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,380
We have to find out
what's going on.

210
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:58,340
<i>(confused murmurs)</i>

211
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,180
What do you
think it means?

212
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:02,920
Princess Twilight
will know.

213
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:05,240
<i>(excited murmurs)</i>

214
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,860
I'm sure it's just...

215
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,340
There's certainly a logical...

216
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:10,880
Your Highness, you
must come with us.

217
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:14,100
<i>(slam)</i>

218
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:16,980
It's Princess Luna and
Princess Celestia.

219
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:18,960
They're gone!

220
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,940
<i>(horrified gasp)</i>

221
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:27,200
<i>TWILIGHT: But I don't</i>
<i>understand. Where are they?</i>

222
00:08:27,260 --> 00:08:28,220
We don't know.

223
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,780
It seems that Princess
Celestia and Princess Luna

224
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,800
have simply...

225
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,460
... <i>vanished</i> .

226
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:34,580
Vanished!

227
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,980
<i>(thud)</i>

228
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,700
This is why we
have come to you.

229
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,880
We await your command.

230
00:08:40,180 --> 00:08:41,980
My command?

231
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:44,500
We're officers of
the Royal Guard.

232
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:46,600
We take our orders
from royalty.

233
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:49,540
With Princess Luna and
Princess Celestia gone

234
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:51,160
and Princess Cadance
overseeing

235
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:52,600
the Crystal Empire now,

236
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:55,520
that means we take our
orders from you.

237
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:56,640
<i>(slap)</i>

238
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:59,700
<i>Princess Twilight, there</i>
<i>is no time to waste.</i>

239
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,840
<i>We need to know what</i>
<i>you want us to do.</i>

240
00:09:04,030 --> 00:09:06,260
I want you to continue the
search for Princess Luna

241
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,400
and Princess Celestia.

242
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:10,020
We have to find them
before ponies start to panic.

243
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,430
There must be some clue
that can tell us

244
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:13,080
what's happened to them.

245
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,020
If you find
something, anything,

246
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:16,670
<i>let me know immediately.</i>

247
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,100
<i>(big sigh)</i>

248
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,650
Way to take
charge, Twilight.

249
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:24,260
Your Highness, news
from Ponyville.

250
00:09:24,410 --> 00:09:27,490
The Everfree Forest
appears to be, well...

251
00:09:28,030 --> 00:09:29,350
...invading!

252
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:30,320
<i>(gasp)</i>

253
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,730
<i>(thud)</i>

254
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:36,070
<i>FLUTTERSHY: Excuse</i>
<i>me. Pardon me.</i>

255
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,800
Are you all right?

256
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:38,910
<i>(chittering)</i>

257
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:40,810
<i>(bleating sheep)</i>

258
00:09:43,060 --> 00:09:45,780
My goodness, what is it
that has caused you all

